text.tspan: UK: Daily new confirmed COVID-19 cases per 100,000
Shown is the rolling 7-day average, by the date a positive specimen is taken; not the date that a case is reported.
The number of confirmed cases is lower than the number of actual cases; the main reason for that is limited testing.
Source: UK Government Coronavirus (COVID-19) Dashboard Last updated 14 December, 18:17 (London time)
